# ── Gemini ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Server-side ONLY. Never prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_ — that would ship the key to
# the browser and let kids (or anyone) bypass the safety gate.
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Model used for the kid-facing conversation.
GEMINI_CHAT_MODEL=gemini-3.5-flash

# Fast/cheap model used for the red-flag safety classifier.
GEMINI_SAFETY_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-lite

# Game-BUILD turns only (middle-path thinking, 2026-07-09): bounded reasoning
# budget + extra output headroom so games match gemini.google.com quality on
# the same model. Ordinary chat is unaffected (thinking stays 0 for instant
# replies). Defaults shown; junk/empty values fall back to them.
# Fallback chain for Gemini 503/429 spikes and model deprecations
# (BUG-FIX-LOG 2026-07-11, PRD-MODEL-FALLBACK): when the primary refuses with
# a capacity error (or its id is retired), we walk this chain — one attempt
# per model — instead of erroring at the kid. Up to 4, comma-separated.
# Default: gemini-3-flash-preview,gemini-2.5-flash,gemini-2.5-flash-lite
# GEMINI_FALLBACK_MODELS=gemini-3-flash-preview,gemini-2.5-flash,gemini-2.5-flash-lite
# GEMINI_BUILDER_THINKING_BUDGET=1024
# GEMINI_BUILDER_MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS=24576

# ── Cross-provider fallback (owner decision 2026-07-20) ──────────────────────
# src/lib/model-registry.ts routes a failed turn to the CHEAPEST model of the
# SAME capability tier, crossing providers freely — quality tier first, price
# within the tier. A provider with no key here is dropped when the chain is
# built, so a failover never discovers a missing key mid-incident.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=      # Claude (prompt-only — see gate below)
# MOONSHOT_API_KEY=       # Kimi   (prompt-only + China data-handling — see below)
#
# Optional base-URL overrides (self-host / regional endpoint / test proxy):
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages
# MOONSHOT_BASE_URL=https://api.moonshot.ai/v1
#
# Pin the chain order explicitly instead of price-sorting (ids must exist in
# MODEL_CATALOG; unknown ids are dropped, never forwarded to an SDK):
# MODEL_FALLBACK_CHAIN=gpt-5.6-luna,gemini-3-flash-preview
#
# ⚠ CHILD-SAFETY GATE — read before setting. Ari's posture (CLAUDE.md §3) is
# input rules → PROVIDER-ENFORCED safety thresholds → child-safety prompt.
# Gemini enforces per-request thresholds (safetySettings); OpenAI is fronted by
# a moderation pass (openai-generation.ts) so its models are `provider-enforced`.
# Anthropic (Claude) and Moonshot (Kimi) have NEITHER — they are `prompt-only`
# and EXCLUDED from every chain unless this flag is exactly "1" AND their key is
# set. Setting it removes the middle safety layer for those models. Do not set
# it in production without an explicit posture decision. Verify the model ids +
# prices in MODEL_CATALOG and run the prompt-portability eval first.
# ALLOW_PROMPT_ONLY_SAFETY_MODELS=1
#
# ⚠ DATA HANDLING — Moonshot (Kimi) is a China-based provider. Sending a child's
# prompts there is a privacy/compliance decision; keep MOONSHOT_API_KEY unset
# until that review, independent of the safety flag above.

# Self-healing preview (docs/FEATURES.md + platform PRD-SELF-HEALING-PREVIEW):
# set to 0 to run INSTRUMENT-ONLY — probes + preview_verify telemetry still
# fire, but broken games are never auto-repaired (no extra Gemini calls).
# Default (unset/anything else) = repair ON, max 2 attempts, 20s bail.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PREVIEW_REPAIR=0

# ── Authentication (Ariantra SSO) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# kidgemini no longer runs its own OAuth. Login happens once on the platform
# (studio.ariantra.com/login — Google OR username/password); the platform sets
# the `ariantra_session` cookie on .ariantra.com and this app verifies it.
#
# AUTH_JWT_SECRET: MUST be the SAME value as the Ariantra-Platform app's
# AUTH_JWT_SECRET (the two apps share the session signature). Server-only.
# Rotating it requires redeploying BOTH apps together.
AUTH_JWT_SECRET=
# Cookie domain the logout route clears (defaults: prod '.ariantra.com', dev host-only).
# SESSION_COOKIE_DOMAIN=.ariantra.com
# Where the sign-in buttons send users (default shown; override for local dev).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARIANTRA_LOGIN_URL=https://studio.ariantra.com/login
# Platform base for the server-to-server publish bridge (default shown).
# LOCAL DEV: set this to your local platform, or every "Put it in the Arcade"
# goes to PRODUCTION and is rejected (dev secret ≠ prod secret) — the publish
# fails with a "check the setup" error (BUG-FIX-LOG 2026-07-11).
# ARIANTRA_API_BASE=https://studio.ariantra.com
# ARIANTRA_API_BASE=http://localhost:3000   # ← local dev

# ── Operator / parent controls ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# The parent PIN is NO LONGER an env var: each family sets a 4-digit PIN on
# their own account (/parent — stored hashed in SQLite parent_auth).
# ADMIN_SECRET gates the /admin usage dashboard (operator-only). No fallback:
# unset means /admin is OFF. Use a long random string.
ADMIN_SECRET=

# USD→INR rate for the /admin dashboard's ₹ figures. NOT a live FX feed —
# update it when the rate moves; unset falls back to the default in
# src/lib/pricing.config.ts. Stored costs stay USD; ₹ derives at read time.
USD_INR_RATE=

# Where the SQLite database file lives (alerts, settings, transcripts).
DATABASE_PATH=./data/kidgemini.db

# ── Payments (Razorpay) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# One-time payment flow (Orders + Checkout). KEY_ID is publishable (the server hands it to the
# browser for Checkout); KEY_SECRET and WEBHOOK_SECRET are server-only — never NEXT_PUBLIC_.
#   Dashboard → Settings → API Keys  (use Test keys in dev, Live keys in prod)
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=
# Webhook signing secret. Dashboard → Settings → Webhooks → add endpoint:
#   https://kidgemini.ariantra.com/api/billing/webhook   (events: payment.captured, order.paid)
# The value below must match the "secret" you set on that webhook.
RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# ── Game-edit patch mode ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Follow-up requests on an existing game are answered with a minimal
# SEARCH/REPLACE patch (untouched parts survive byte-for-byte), with a strict
# hunks-only retry when the model tries to rewrite the whole file.
# Set to "off" to restore exact pre-patch behavior (full regeneration on every
# follow-up, as before 2026-07-18). Any other value (or unset) = enabled.
GAME_EDIT_PATCH=
